(This can happen when the recovered key is an existing additional miner key outside canonical) Tj
T*
(slots \(for example miner_3\). On current builds, this path is reported as informational) Tj
T*
(\(Recovered existing key outside canonical miner slots.\). If you still see the old warning,) Tj
T*
(update to the latest code and restart the wallet API process.) Tj
T*
(- **Key manager startup fails with schema validation error:** The key file failed strict) Tj
T*
(structure validation. Check Keys/backups/ for the last known backup, repair malformed records,) Tj
T*
(and restart. Runtime now fails closed instead of silently accepting malformed key JSON.) Tj
T*
(- **unsupported hash type during mnemonic operations:** On some Python/OpenSSL builds, native) Tj
T*
(pbkdf2_hmac\('sha3_512'\) is unavailable. Install project dependencies \(cryptography\) so the) Tj
T*
(accelerated SHA3-512 PBKDF2 path is used.) Tj
T*
(- **Cannot delete address:** Deletion is blocked only if it would remove the last key on the) Tj
T*
(selected network. Ensure at least two keys exist; defaults are reassigned automatically when one) Tj
T*
(is removed.) Tj
T*
(- **Hashrate stuck / no blocks:** Verify mining is enabled, check logs for PoW errors, and) Tj
T*
(ensure the mempool isn?t rejecting constructed blocks.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Docker / Compose) Tj
T*
(- **Port binding errors:** If a host port is in use, remove the mapping or use random host ports) Tj
T*
(\(e.g., ports: ["10200"]\). P2P ports are fixed \(56000 in-container; host binds) Tj
T*
(56000/56001/56002/56003\).) Tj
T*
(- **API key missing in containers:** Entry point auto-creates one; read logs for the generated) Tj
T*
(key/user/pass. Ensure Src/Config is mounted.) Tj
T*
(- **Containers not following host chain:** Set ATHO_BOOTSTRAP=host.docker.internal:56000 \(or) Tj
T*
(your LAN IP\) and wipe peers/storage before docker compose up.) Tj
T*
(- **Modules missing in container:** Rebuild after updating requirements.txt \(docker compose) Tj
T*
(build --no-cache\); ensure Python is 3.11 in the image.) Tj
T*
(- **Random API ports on miners:** Discover with docker compose port miner 10200 \(and ... 10250) Tj
T*
(for miner2\) when host ports are randomized.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Build / Tooling) Tj
T*
(- **falcon_cli build fails:** Install toolchain \(build-essential/clang/libssl-dev on Linux;) Tj
T*
(Xcode CLT on macOS\). On ARM, disable AVX2 \(FALCON_USE_AVX2=false\). Use Docker to avoid local) Tj
T*
(toolchain issues.) Tj
T*
(- **falcon_cli pinning is required but no expected digest is configured**: Update) Tj
T*
(Constants.FALCONCLI_PINNED_VERSION_DIGESTS in Src/Utility/const.py for the active) Tj
T*
(CONSENSUS_VERSION, using the release-audited version-bound digest. Mainnet/testnet startup is) Tj
T*
(intentionally blocked until this is set.) Tj
T*
(- **Runtime guard fail-closed startup error:** If startup reports runtime guard bootstrap) Tj
T*
(failure, inspect logs/<network>/security/security.log, verify Src/Config/security_manifest.json,) Tj
T*
(and ensure ATHO_RUNTIME_GUARD_RELEASE_PUBKEY_HEX matches release signer pubkey when signature is) Tj
T*
(required.) Tj
T*
(- **runtime_guard_violation during runtime:** In enforce mode this is expected fail-closed) Tj
T*
(behavior on drift. Re-deploy clean artifacts, re-verify manifest, and restart nodes from trusted) Tj
T*
(release package.) Tj
T*
(- **python not found / deps missing:** Use Python 3.11+, activate venv, pip install -r) Tj
T*
(requirements.txt.) Tj
T*
(- **LibreSSL/SSL warnings:** Typically harmless locally; if you see handshake errors, upgrade) Tj
T*
(OpenSSL/Python.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Dependency install issues \(venv + pip\)) Tj
T*
(- **Use a virtual environment first \(strongly recommended\)**) Tj
T*
(- Why: avoids global package conflicts and broken mixed installs.) Tj
